         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the Divine Spirits. Hedone lived for ten years, five months, (and) six
               days. Lucius Vivius Antiochus made (this) for his homeborn slave, by leave of Marcus
               Popidius Natalis.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>In line 6, while “ex” should take an ablative, it is a common enough mistake for it to take an accusative instead.
                      (Dessau ILS vol. 3 p. 865)
                   </p>
